# Commit Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <body>
# <BLANK LINE>
# <footer>

# Types:
#   feat     - New feature for Cherry-101
#   fix      - Bug fix in CherryScript implementation
#   docs     - Documentation only changes
#   style    - Code formatting, missing semicolons, etc.
#   refactor - Code restructuring, no functionality change
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Build process or auxiliary tool changes
#   ml       - Machine Learning/AutoML related changes
#   db       - Database adapter changes
#   deploy   - Deployment/Endpoint related changes
#   parser   - Parser or interpreter changes
#   runtime  - Runtime environment changes

# Scopes:
#   cherry   - CherryScript language core
#   adapter  - Database/ML/Deployment adapters
#   cli      - Command Line Interface
#   examples - Example scripts and demos
#   docker   - Containerization
#   docs     - Documentation
#   tests    - Test suite

# Examples:
#   feat(parser): Add support for for-loops in CherryScript
#   fix(adapter): Resolve MySQL connection timeout issue
#   docs(examples): Add Cherry-101 tutorial with step-by-step guide
#   ml(adapter): Improve H2O AutoML integration performance

# Subject Line Guidelines:
# - Use imperative mood: "Add feature" not "Added feature"
# - First letter lowercase
# - No period at end
# - Keep under 72 characters

# Body Guidelines:
# - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# - Reference issue numbers when applicable
# - Wrap at 72 characters

# Footer Guidelines:
# - Reference GitHub issues: "Fixes #123"
# - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: <explanation>"

